                        <p class="tpr-article-content__paragraph tpr-article-content__paragraph--blog">Hakeem is about British-Jamaican singer-songwriter and poet, Hak Baker. The film chronicles his unexpected yet remarkable rise to fame: from winning a guitar in a prison raffle to performing for a sold-out crowd at The Royal Albert Hall. Hakeem is the feature documentary debut of DEADHORSES (James Topley and Ivo Beckett), who have worked with artists such as Sam Fender and Pete Doherty (The Libertines). Filmed over five years and made from over 500 hours of home video footage, the documentary gives an insight into Hak Baker’s life growing up in East London’s Isle of Dogs and explores brotherhood, the nuances of British 'lad culture' and mental health struggles.</p>

